# /etc/cogno/cogno.env — systemd EnvironmentFile for cogno-node.service. Copy to /etc/cogno/cogno.env,
# fill in DBSYNC_URL, then lock it down (it can carry the db-sync password):
#
#     install -o root -g cogno -m 0640 deploy/systemd/cogno.env.example /etc/cogno/cogno.env
#     sudoedit /etc/cogno/cogno.env   # stays root:cogno 0640 — readable only by the service user
#
# The all-Rust node is the whole deployment: it reads ONLY these two variables from this file. There is
# no relayer / follower / indexer / committee daemon any more, so there are no signing seeds, no Ogmios,
# and no indexer Postgres here — privileged calls are made ad hoc by `cogno-chain-cli` (keys by file, off
# this host), and the L1 tx submit / cost-model path (Ogmios / Blockfrost) belongs to the CLI + frontend,
# not to a service. NEVER commit a filled-in copy (DBSYNC_URL may embed a password).

# ── cardano: db-sync (the sole Cardano data layer) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Read-only Cardano db-sync (Postgres) — the SOLE Cardano data layer. The node's in-protocol observer
# (D4) reads the talk_vault here (the deterministic block-at/before-slot reference + the vault UTxO read:
# spentness from tx_in, coins as ::text, driven from the indexed payment_cred). Absent / unset ⇒ the
# observer ABSTAINS (the chain still produces + finalizes; talk-stake weight simply goes stale). The unit's
# `EnvironmentFile=-` makes a missing file / unset value non-fatal. MAINNET PREREQUISITE: db-sync FULL
# (non-pruned, retaining history back to the reference), tx_in-enabled (NOT --consumed-tx-out — the read
# probes EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM tx_in) and abstains fail-closed otherwise), and over TLS.
DBSYNC_URL=postgres://cogno_reader:PASSWORD@127.0.0.1:5432/cexplorer

# ── logging (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Standard env_logger filter for the node + pallets (per-target LOG_TARGETs). Leave unset for defaults.
# RUST_LOG=info,cardano_observer=debug
